sameAnalysis.part_name: 这些名词都有"女性"之意。
means: female与male"男(性)的，公的，雄的"相对，强调性别，可指人或动物，但除用于科学和统计上外，大多含贬义。

entry.def: Someone who is female is a woman or a girl.

example.ex: ...a sixteen-piece dance band with a female singer...
example.tran: 16 人组成的伴舞乐队和一位女歌手

example.ex: Their aim is equal numbers of male and female MPs by the year 2000...
example.tran: 他们的目标是 2000 年前使国会议员中男女人数相等。

entry.def: Women and girls are sometimes referred to as females when they are being considered as a type.

example.ex: But the average young female in this country now is stylish and remarkably confident...
example.tran: 但该国普通年轻女子现在都非常时髦，而且极其自信。

example.ex: Hay fever affects males more than females.
example.tran: 男性的花粉热感染率比女性高。

entry.def: Female matters and things relate to, belong to, or affect women rather than men.
You can refer to any creature that can lay eggs or produce babies from its body as a female .

example.ex: Each female will lay just one egg in April or May.

entry.def: A female flower or plant contains the part that will become the fruit when it is fertilized.

example.ex: Figs have male and female flowers.

2. a person who belongs to the sex that can have babies

3. for or composed of women or girls;
